article.headline: Princeton 75, Columbia 64
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Noah Savage scored 18 points as Princeton broke a nine-game losing streak with a 75-64 win over Columbia on Friday night. Zach Woolridge added 15 and Kareem Maddox had 14 as the Tigers (6-21, 3-9 Ivy League) defeated Columbia for the 15th straight time at Jadwin Gym. John Baumann had a game-high 21 points to lead Columbia (14-14, 7-6), while Niko Scott added 20 for the Lions. Princeton, which shot 53 percent for the game, took a 38-30 lead into halftime. Columbia cut the margin to 38-34 early in the second half before a 7-0 Tigers run, capped by a Maddox three-point play, gave the Tigers a double-digit lead at 45-34. Princeton converted 18 of 22 free throw attempts to help keep the Lions at bay.
